01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:37,290
How nice of you to join us here!
你真高兴加入我们吧！

1324
01:29:37,330 --> 01:29:40,030
Listen, I think I got something. You need a dermatologist?
听着，我想我有所收获。你需要皮肤科医生吗？

1325
01:29:40,290 --> 01:29:41,610
Don't tell me, I'll get it.
不要告诉我，我会明白的。

1326
01:29:41,790 --> 01:29:44,080
George Raft! Right? Where the hell have you been?
乔治筏！对？你到底去了哪里？

1327
01:29:44,120 --> 01:29:45,170
I have to talk to you.
我得和你谈谈。

1328
01:29:45,200 --> 01:29:48,410
I think I'm onto something. It could be your actual ball game. I mean it.
我想我正在做点什么。这可能是你真正的球赛。我是认真的。

1329
01:29:48,450 --> 01:29:50,700
Golly, gee, Scoop, that sounds very interesting!
Golly，gee，Scoop，听起来很有趣！

1330
01:29:50,910 --> 01:29:52,540
Something is wrong. Something big.
出了点问题。有点大。

1331
01:29:52,580 --> 01:29:54,710
They know I'm onto it and they tried to kill me.
他们知道我在上面，他们试图杀了我。

1332
01:29:54,740 --> 01:29:56,330
Who's they? I can't tell you.
他们是谁？我不能告诉你。

1333
01:29:56,360 --> 01:29:57,910
Why not? You wouldn't believe me.
为什么不？你不会相信我。

1334
01:29:57,950 --> 01:29:59,030
You don't think so?
你不这么认为吗？

1335
01:29:59,540 --> 01:30:01,620
Okay, listen to me. I got a tip from a friend,
好的，听我说?我得到了一位朋友，

1336
01:30:01,660 --> 01:30:03,330
a good friend, then he disappeared.
一位好朋友的小费，然后他消失了。

1337
01:30:03,370 --> 01:30:04,290
Disappeared?
消失了？

1338
01:30:04,330 --> 01:30:07,580
Like he never existed. There's some lady living in his apartment.
就像他从未存在过一样。有一位女士住在他的公寓里。

1339
01:30:07,620 --> 01:30:09,130
His apartment is all different.
他的公寓各不相同。

1340
01:30:09,160 --> 01:30:11,580
She said she's been living there for more than a year.
她说她已经在那里生活了一年多。

1341
01:30:11,620 --> 01:30:13,420
I checked the building rental office.
我检查了大楼租赁办公室。

1342
01:30:13,460 --> 01:30:15,920
They have receipts from her for more than a year.
他们收到了一年多的收据。

1343
01:30:15,950 --> 01:30:17,210
I checked NAS A personnel.
我检查了NAS A人员。

1344
01:30:17,250 --> 01:30:19,920
They have no record my friend ever worked there.
他们没有记录我的朋友在那里工作过。

1345
01:30:19,950 --> 01:30:21,620
They say they never even heard of him.
他们说他们从未听说过他。

1346
01:30:21,660 --> 01:30:22,800
So this friend of yours,
所以你的朋友，你

1347
01:30:22,830 --> 01:30:25,590
who works at NAS A, gives you a tip, then disappears.
在NAS A工作，给你一个提示，然后消失。

1348
01:30:25,620 --> 01:30:29,080
And it turns out that he never lived in his apartment or worked at NAS A.
事实证明，他从未住在他的公寓里或在NAS A工作过。

1349
01:30:29,120 --> 01:30:31,750
This is the guy that gave you the tip on your cosmic scoop,
这就是那个给你提示宇宙勺子的人，

1350
01:30:31,790 --> 01:30:33,710
and you think I won't believe you? My car!
而你认为我不相信你？我的车！

1351
01:30:33,740 --> 01:30:35,260
Someone tampered with my car!
有人篡改了我的车！

1352
01:30:35,290 --> 01:30:37,090
The one you decided to go swimming with?
你决定去游泳的那个？

1353
01:30:37,130 --> 01:30:39,290
They did something to it! I couldn't stop it!
他们做了些什么！我无法阻止它！

1354
01:30:39,330 --> 01:30:40,410
Can you prove that?
你能证明吗？

1355
01:30:42,630 --> 01:30:44,000
The police said...
警方说......?

1356
01:30:45,580 --> 01:30:49,210
They said that nothing was wrong. And you think I won't believe you.
他们说没有错。而且你认为我不会相信你。

1357
01:30:49,250 --> 01:30:50,580
Somebody took a shot at me!
有人对我开枪！

1358
01:30:50,620 --> 01:30:51,880
When? Yesterday.
什么时候？昨天。

1359
01:30:51,920 --> 01:30:54,700
Thank God, I've got an alibi! I'm telling you the truth!
感谢上帝，我有一个不在犯罪现场！我告诉你实话！

1360
01:30:55,540 --> 01:30:58,160
Listen to me and listen good.
听我说，听好。

1361
01:31:00,040 --> 01:31:03,130
I don't like you, Caulfield. You're ambitious.
考菲尔德，我不喜欢你。你雄心勃勃。

1362
01:31:03,500 --> 01:31:06,950
You think the way to get ahead is to come up with the scoop of the century.
你认为获得成功的方法是提出本世纪的独家新闻。

1363
01:31:07,170 --> 01:31:10,630
Woodward and Bernstein were good reporters. That's how they did it.
伍德沃德和伯恩斯坦都是好记者。他们就是这样做的。

1364
01:31:10,670 --> 01:31:14,170
Not by telling me they've located Patty Hearst three times, like you did.
不是告诉我他们已经找到帕蒂赫斯特三次，

1365
01:31:14,380 --> 01:31:17,970
Or that brilliant piece of investigative journalism you pulled off,
或者

1366
01:31:18,000 --> 01:31:21,630
by finding an eyewitness to the 2nd gunman in the Kennedy assassination.
通过在肯尼迪遇刺事件中找到第二名枪手的目击者，你发现了这部精彩的调查性新闻。

1367
01:31:21,670 --> 01:31:25,250
The small fact that the man had been in a mental institution at the time,
那个男人当时在精神病院里的一个小事实，

1368
01:31:25,290 --> 01:31:27,790
never deterred you, not Scoop Caulfield!
从来没有吓到过你，不是Scoop Caulfield！

1369
01:31:29,380 --> 01:31:32,640
Now, most reporters are like me. They are plodders.
现在，大多数记者都像我一样。他们是笨蛋。

1370
01:31:32,670 --> 01:31:36,710
They spend a lot of their time checking little things..., like facts.
他们花了很多时间检查小事......就像事实一样。

1371
01:31:37,010 --> 01:31:40,090
They cover mundane stories like wars,
它们涵盖了战争，

1372
01:31:40,550 --> 01:31:42,090
and trials and hearings.
审判和听证等世俗故事。

1373
01:31:42,710 --> 01:31:45,710
You never seem to have enough time in your busy schedule
在忙碌的日程中

1374
01:31:45,750 --> 01:31:48,670
to stoop so low as to cover a story.
，你似乎没有足够的时间来弯腰以至于无法掩盖一个故事。

1375
01:31:49,050 --> 01:31:52,930
You occupy your time with tips from people who never existed,
你可以从那些从未存在过的人那里获取技巧，

1376
01:31:52,960 --> 01:31:56,590
driving your car into water and then claiming it wasn't your fault,
将你的车开入水中然后声称这不是你的错，

1377
01:31:56,630 --> 01:31:58,550
getting shot at by unseen gunmen.
被看不见的枪手射杀。

1378
01:31:59,220 --> 01:32:02,730
Now, I really hate to interrupt your meteoric career
现在，我真的很讨厌以

1379
01:32:02,770 --> 01:32:06,250
with something so plebeian as a legitimate story.
一种如此平凡的合法故事打断你的流星生涯。

1380
01:32:06,590 --> 01:32:07,620
However,
然而，

1381
01:32:07,920 --> 01:32:10,890
a trainload of propane gas had the bad taste
一连串的丙烷气体

1382
01:32:10,920 --> 01:32:15,050
to derail near Galveston and there's a whole town that just might blow up.
在加尔维斯顿附近出现了不好的味道，并且整个城镇可能会爆炸。

1383
01:32:15,630 --> 01:32:18,310
So it would be just really peachy or you
所以，

1384
01:32:18,340 --> 01:32:21,720
if you would join you film crew that's waiting for you on the plane
如果你愿意和我一起参加你在飞机

1385
01:32:21,750 --> 01:32:23,620
at this very moment while we speak.
上等待你的电影工作人员，那我们说话的时候真是太好了。

1386
01:32:24,800 --> 01:32:26,790
That was a speech. I thought so.
那是一个演讲。我是这么想的。

1387
01:32:27,260 --> 01:32:29,720
I cannot go to Galveston right now.
我现在不能去加尔维斯顿。

1388
01:32:29,750 --> 01:32:30,830
I don't think I heard you.
我不认为我听到了你。

1389
01:32:31,510 --> 01:32:32,420
Look,
看，

1390
01:32:32,720 --> 01:32:35,810
when a reporter tells his Assignment Editor
当记者告诉他的任务编辑时

1391
01:32:35,840 --> 01:32:39,460
that he thinks he may be onto something that could be really big,
，他认为他可能会做一些可能非常大的事情，

1392
01:32:39,680 --> 01:32:41,970
the Assignment Editor's suppose to say,
作业编辑假设说，

1393
01:32:42,010 --> 01:32:43,560
'You got forty-eight hours, kid,
'你有四十八个小时，孩子，

1394
01:32:43,590 --> 01:32:45,430
and you better come up with something good
你最好拿出一些好东西，

1395
01:32:45,460 --> 01:32:46,640
or it's gonna be your neck.'
或者它会成为你的脖子。

1396
01:32:46,680 --> 01:32:49,140
That's what he's supposed to say! I saw it in a movie!
这就是他应该说的！我在电影里看到了它！

1397
01:32:49,170 --> 01:32:50,700
Get your ass on that plane!
在那架飞机上得到你的屁股！

1398
01:32:50,730 --> 01:32:52,180
I can't! I have to follow this!
我不能！我必须遵循这个！

1399
01:32:52,220 --> 01:32:54,910
And you can't tell me what this earth-shattering story is?
你不能告诉我这个惊天动地的故事是什么？

1400
01:32:54,940 --> 01:32:57,590
It sounds too crazy. If I told you, I'd be in more trouble.
听起来太疯狂了。如果我告诉你，我会遇到麻烦。

1401
01:32:57,630 --> 01:33:00,550
You're not crazy! I'm crazy! I'm crazy for listening!
你不是疯了！我疯了！我很难听！

1402
01:33:00,590 --> 01:33:02,980
And I'm crazy for saying what I'm about to say!
而且我很想说我要说的话！

1403
01:33:03,010 --> 01:33:05,480
I'll give you twenty-four hours come up with something!
我会给你二十四小时的东西！

1404
01:33:05,510 --> 01:33:08,790
Not forty-eight! I saw the movie, too, and it was twenty-four!
不是四十八岁！我也看过电影，那是二十四岁！

1405
01:34:18,770 --> 01:34:19,760
Freeze!
冻结！

1406
01:34:20,560 --> 01:34:22,770
I'm not moving an inch. Robert Caulfield?
一世'?我不动一寸。罗伯特考菲尔德？

1407
01:34:22,800 --> 01:34:24,850
Yeah, who the hell are you? Federal Agents.
是的，你到底是谁？联邦特工。

1408
01:34:24,890 --> 01:34:26,860
We have a warrant to search your apartment.
我们有权搜查您的公寓。

1409
01:34:26,890 --> 01:34:30,060
You have a warrant? What for? Just don't move.
你有权证吗？做什么的？只是不要动。

1410
01:34:30,350 --> 01:34:32,600
I promise. Just tell me what this is all about.
我承诺。告诉我这是什么。

1411
01:34:32,640 --> 01:34:34,010
Hey, come here! Look at this!
嘿，过来！看这个！

1412
01:34:34,190 --> 01:34:36,260
Could you come with me, please, Mr. Caulfield?
考希尔德先生，请你跟我来吗？

1413
01:35:05,810 --> 01:35:07,640
Mr. Caulfield, I'm sorry.
考尔菲尔德先生，对不起。

1414
01:35:08,150 --> 01:35:10,900
However, you're under arrest for possession of cocaine.
但是，你因藏有可卡因而被捕。

1415
01:35:11,230 --> 01:35:12,430
I don't believe it.
我不相信。

1416
01:35:13,360 --> 01:35:15,970
I don't believe it. You guys put it there, you know you did.
我不相信。你们把它放在那里，你知道你做到了。

1417
01:35:16,480 --> 01:35:18,190
You have the right to remain silent.
你有保持沉默的权利。

1418
01:35:21,230 --> 01:35:24,480
You have the right to an attorney. I don't believe it. You put it there.
您有权获得律师。我不相信。你把它放在那里。

1419
01:35:24,520 --> 01:35:27,180
Anything you say may be held against you in a court of law.
你说的任何话都可能在法庭上对你不利。

1420
01:35:27,730 --> 01:35:30,600
You're part of all this. You mothers.
你是这一切的一部分。你妈妈?

1421
01:35:31,860 --> 01:35:33,050
Ow, that hurts!
喔，那很疼！

1422
01:35:33,320 --> 01:35:34,990
You don't have to put handcuffs on me!
你不必把手铐放在我身上！

1423
01:35:35,020 --> 01:35:37,820
Please, Mr. Caulfield, these are serious charges against you.
请考虑先生，这些是对你的严重指控。

1424
01:35:37,860 --> 01:35:41,020
Don't add to them by resisting arrest. I don't bel...! That hurts!
不要通过抵制逮捕来增加它们。我不喜欢......！那伤害了！

1425
01:35:41,860 --> 01:35:43,350
I don't believe this.
我不相信这一点。

1426
01:35:52,320 --> 01:35:55,180
Well, hello there, Caulfield! So nice to see you!
好吧，你好，Caulfield！很高兴见到你！

1427
01:35:55,780 --> 01:35:59,140
It's at this point that Alan Hale says to Richard Conte...
正是在这一点上，艾伦黑尔对理查德孔蒂说...?

1428
01:35:59,730 --> 01:36:02,050
Jimmy Stewart. Yeah, Jimmy Stewart, thank you.
吉米斯图尔特。是的，吉米斯图尔特，谢谢你。

1429
01:36:02,080 --> 01:36:04,360
Look, Scoop, I can't keep bailing you out of trouble.
看，Scoop，我不能让你摆脱困境。

1430
01:36:04,400 --> 01:36:05,740
The front office is on my neck.
前厅在我的脖子上。

1431
01:36:05,780 --> 01:36:08,980
I don't know how much longer I can keep them off, right?
我不知道能把它们关掉多久，对吧？

1432
01:36:09,020 --> 01:36:09,950
Right. Wrong!
对。错误！

1433
01:36:09,990 --> 01:36:12,690
I got you out of there so as not to embarrass the Network.
我让你离开那里，以免让网络难堪。

1434
01:36:12,730 --> 01:36:15,400
I mean, you are a schmuck! I can't trust you to cover a fire!
我的意思是，你是个笨蛋！我不能相信你掩盖火灾！

1435
01:36:15,440 --> 01:36:17,400
You'll probably fall down and get burned!
你可能会摔倒并被烧伤！

1436
01:36:17,440 --> 01:36:19,360
You probably would be the cause of it!
你可能会成为它的原因！

1437
01:36:19,400 --> 01:36:21,480
A company car? You are fired!
公司的车？你被开除了！

1438
01:36:21,610 --> 01:36:24,820
I love that so much! I'm gonna say it again!
我非常喜欢这个！我要再说一遍了！

1439
01:36:24,860 --> 01:36:28,030
You're fired! You're through! Oh, I love it!
你被开除了！你通过了！哦，我喜欢它！

1440
01:36:28,060 --> 01:36:29,910
It's not what it looks like, really.
真的，它不是它的样子。

1441
01:36:29,940 --> 01:36:32,230
'Frankly, Scarlet, I don't give a damn!'
“坦率地说，斯卡雷特，我不会诅咒！”?

1442
01:36:34,950 --> 01:36:38,200
I told you. You tell me about the lonely plight of a dedicated journalist.
我告诉你了。你告诉我一位专职记者的孤独困境。

1443
01:36:38,230 --> 01:36:39,280
I tell you to stuff it.
我告诉你这件事。

1444
01:36:39,320 --> 01:36:41,240
You tell me about a meaningful relationship.
你告诉我一段有意义的关系。

1445
01:36:41,270 --> 01:36:42,490
I tell you to stuff it.
我告诉你这件事。

1446
01:36:42,530 --> 01:36:44,740
You tell me you're in trouble, you're out on bail,
你告诉我你有困难，你被保释，

1447
01:36:44,770 --> 01:36:46,950
you just got fired, I tell you I'll be right over.
你被解雇了，我告诉你我会马上结束。

1448
01:36:46,980 --> 01:36:48,700
My head hurts. You look awful.
我头疼。你看起来很可怕。

1449
01:36:48,740 --> 01:36:50,740
Thank you, very much. You're quite welcome.
非常感谢你。你太客气了。

1450
01:36:50,770 --> 01:36:52,110
Did you find out what I asked?
你知道我问了什么吗？

1451
01:36:52,410 --> 01:36:55,660
One o'clock in the morning I get a call from an unemployed junkie
凌晨一点钟，我接到一名失业的瘾君子打来电话

1452
01:36:55,690 --> 01:36:58,910
to find out all the military installations in a 300 miles radius
，找出

1453
01:36:58,940 --> 01:36:59,910
around Houston, Texas.
德克萨斯州休斯顿周围300英里范围内的所有军事设施。

1454
01:36:59,950 --> 01:37:02,630
You certainly have a way with words. Did you find out?
你当然有办法说文字。你知道了吗？

1455
01:37:02,670 --> 01:37:05,320
Yes, and it wasn't easy. It took exhaustive research.
是的，这并不容易。它进行了详尽的研究。

1456
01:37:05,530 --> 01:37:07,200
Well, I'm proud of you. How many?
好吧，我为你感到骄傲。多少？

1457
01:37:07,240 --> 01:37:10,910
One. White Bluff. It's a S AC base. My father used to be stationed there.
一。白崖。这是一个S AC基地。我父亲曾经驻扎在那里。

1458
01:37:10,940 --> 01:37:12,610
That's exhaustive research?
这是详尽的研究？

1459
01:37:12,700 --> 01:37:15,870
At one o'clock in the morning, you call your father, that's exhaustive.
在凌晨一点，你打电话给你的父亲，这是详尽无遗的。

1460
01:37:15,900 --> 01:37:18,120
White Bluff... That's too big. Too big for what?
怀特布拉夫......那太大了。什么太大了？

1461
01:37:18,150 --> 01:37:20,320
Too big for what I want. What do you want?
太大了我想要的东西。你想要什么？

1462
01:37:20,360 --> 01:37:21,790
I'm thinking of enlisting.
我想要招募。

1463
01:37:21,820 --> 01:37:24,620
They'll never take you. That's why I'm thinking of enlisting.
他们永远不会带你。这就是我想要招募的原因。

1464
01:37:24,650 --> 01:37:27,000
You're on a story, aren't you? I was fired!
你是故事，不是吗？我被解雇！

1465
01:37:27,030 --> 01:37:29,820
You're on a story and I'm helping you. This can't be happening.
你是一个故事，我在帮助你。这不可能发生。

1466
01:37:29,860 --> 01:37:31,080
I really appreciate that.
我真的很感激。

1467
01:37:31,120 --> 01:37:33,740
The only reason I'm doing it, considering your track record,
我这样做的唯一原因，考虑到你的记录，

1468
01:37:33,780 --> 01:37:36,530
whatever story you're on will turn out to be garbage.
无论你在哪个故事，都会变成垃圾。

1469
01:37:36,570 --> 01:37:38,190
You shouldn't mince words.
你不应该贬低言辞。

1470
01:37:45,280 --> 01:37:47,490
I'll fix you some coffee. Then you can jump me.
我会给你一些咖啡。然后你可以跳我。

1471
01:37:47,830 --> 01:37:49,860
There's no other one besides White Bluff?
除了怀特布拉夫之外别无他人？

1472
01:37:50,120 --> 01:37:51,030
No.
